text: Sierah Catherine "Ce" Joughin (February 11, 1996 â€“ July 22, 2016) was an American woman who was abducted and murdered in Delta, Ohio. She disappeared on July 19, 2016, and was found dead three days later. Her assailant, James D. Worley, was convicted and sentenced to death for the murder and over twenty years in prison for the kidnapping, assault, and other related charges. His execution is currently scheduled for May 20, 2025. Category:1996 births Category:2016 deaths Category:2016 crimes
